Definitions:

Berkeley DB query 
    The XQuery sent to the XML database to retrieve data about the BES Attributes Documents. 

informationService-service-path 
    The RNS path to the Information Service whose XML collection you would like to query. 

Description:

The xmldb-query command is used to query the Berkley XML Database where you have stored the Attributes Documents of the BES containers you are currently watching in your Information Service.

Code:

Implementing Class 
    edu.virginia.vcgr.genii.client.cmd.tools.InfoSQueryTool 

Example:

xmldb-query "" /MyIS


This query will return all the documents stored in the collection created for the Information Service resource MyIS 
